 coarse reconstruction, and reconstruction error. I also wired a default `operator_qa_dir` config path and `make operator-qa`.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-004_Add_configurable_boundary-condition_and_anisotropy_plumbing_to_operator_assembly/prompt.md:1:Work ticket FW-M6-004: Add configurable boundary-condition and anisotropy plumbing to operator assembly.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-004_Add_configurable_boundary-condition_and_anisotropy_plumbing_to_operator_assembly/prompt.md:4:Source: Milestone 6 roadmap 2026-03-21\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-004_Add_configurable_boundary-condition_and_anisotropy_plumbing_to_operator_assembly/prompt.md:10:The roadmap explicitly calls for boundary masks and optional anisotropy tensors, but the current pipeline has no stable way to describe or assemble either. If Milestone 6 ships only a hardcoded isotropic operator with implicit boundary behavior, Milestones 10 and 13 will have to reopen the asset contract and retroactively guess how directional propagation or boundary semantics were supposed to work.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-004_Add_configurable_boundary-condition_and_anisotropy_plumbing_to_operator_assembly/last_message.md:1:Implemented FW-M6-004 end to end.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-005_Ship_operator_quality_metrics_pulse-propagation_smoke_tests_and_offline_inspection_tooling/prompt.md:1:Work ticket FW-M6-005: Ship operator quality metrics, pulse-propagation smoke tests, and offline inspection tooling.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-005_Ship_operator_quality_metrics_pulse-propagation_smoke_tests_and_offline_inspection_tooling/prompt.md:4:Source: Milestone 6 roadmap 2026-03-21\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-005_Ship_operator_quality_metrics_pulse-propagation_smoke_tests_and_offline_inspection_tooling/prompt.md:10:Milestone 6 is only complete if the team can initialize a pulse on one neuron, verify that surface propagation behaves stably enough for later engine work, compare coarse and fine operators quantitatively, and inspect the results without digging through raw arrays. Right now there is no standard harness that exercises those numerical behaviors, no operator quality report, and no offline visualization flow for reviewing what the assembled operators are actually doing on the mesh.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-005_Ship_operator_quality_metrics_pulse-propagation_smoke_tests_and_offline_inspection_tooling/prompt.md:13:Add a Milestone 6 validation and inspection workflow that consumes local operator bundles and produces actionable diagnostics. The workflow should initialize localized test fields, run a lightweight stability-oriented evolution or repeated operator application suitable for pre-engine validation, compute operator quality metrics, and generate an offline report that overlays relevant outputs on the mesh and patch decomposition. The goal is not to build the final wave engine; it is to make operator quality, pulse localization, and coarse-versus-fine behavior inspectable and regression-testable before Milestone 10 begins.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-005_Ship_operator_quality_metrics_pulse-propagation_smoke_tests_and_offline_inspection_tooling/prompt.md:27:Assume the earlier Milestone 6 tickets have already landed. Favor lightweight offline artifacts such as Markdown plus images, HTML, or another review-friendly format that can be attached to run logs without special infrastructure.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/last_message.md:1:Implemented FW-M6-002.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/last_message.md:5:- Wired the build path through [mesh_pipeline.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/mesh_pipeline.py), [geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/geometry_contract.py), and [03_build_wave_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py) so the script remains orchestration-only and `operator_bundle.assets.fine_operator` now points at the dedicated artifact. The coarse operator remains the patch-graph alias for now.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/prompt.md:1:Work ticket FW-M6-002: Assemble fine-surface operators with geodesic neighborhoods, tangent frames, and boundary masks.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/prompt.md:4:Source: Milestone 6 roadmap 2026-03-21\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/prompt.md:10:The current processed surface graph is still a Milestone 5 scaffold. It exposes simplified mesh connectivity and a uniform graph Laplacian, but it does not yet provide the numerical objects Milestone 6 actually needs: geodesic neighborhoods, boundary masks, local tangent frames, metric-aware weights, or a surface operator whose supporting geometry is explicit enough to debug and validate. That leaves the repo unable to build a simulation-ready single-neuron surface state without rewriting the existing graph archive by hand.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/prompt.md:13:Implement the fine-surface operator builder that turns a simplified mesh bundle into a numerically meaningful fine-resolution operator artifact. Use the discretization family chosen in `FW-M6-001`, and serialize the supporting geometry needed to inspect or reuse the operator later: adjacency and edge geometry, local areas or mass terms, normals and tangent frames, geodesic-neighborhood structures, and boundary masks. Keep sparse assembly in library code, make the script layer an orchestrator only, and ensure the output is deterministic for the same mesh and config.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-002_Assemble_fine-surface_operators_with_geodesic_neighborhoods_tangent_frames_and_boundary_masks/prompt.md:27:Assume `FW-M6-001` is already in place. Favor inspectable sparse formats and explicit metadata over opaque archives that require reverse-engineering at read time.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-004_Add_derived_geometry_descriptors_and_simplification_QA_with_documented_error_budgets/prompt.md:18:- Default QA thresholds and descriptor rationale are documented in a dedicated markdown note aimed at later Milestone 6 and Milestone 11 consumers.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-004_Add_derived_geometry_descriptors_and_simplification_QA_with_documented_error_budgets/prompt.md:27:Keep the first descriptor set pragmatic rather than exhaustive. Favor metrics that are cheap to compute locally and easy to explain in docs, then leave room for future expansion if Milestone 6 needs more physically specific fidelity checks.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-004_Add_derived_geometry_descriptors_and_simplification_QA_with_documented_error_budgets/stdout.jsonl:8:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_2\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \\\"simplif|patch|asset|descriptor|summary|mesh|skeleton|qa|threshold\\\" src tests scripts docs config manifests schemas Makefile'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"Makefile:8:.PHONY: help bootstrap verify registry select meshes assets validate-manifest test smoke all\\nMakefile:18:\\t\\t'meshes             Fetch raw meshes and optional skeletons' \\\\\\nMakefile:19:\\t\\t'