{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_149","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the Milestone 6 verification pass end-to-end.\n\nI added a shipped readiness workflow in [07_milestone6_readiness.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/07_milestone6_readiness.py) and [milestone6_readiness.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/milestone6_readiness.py), plus the tracked offline config [milestone_6_verification.yaml](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/config/milestone_6_verification.yaml) and `make milestone6-readiness`. I also hardened real-mesh assembly in [mesh_pipeline.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/mesh_pipeline.py), [surface_operators.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/surface_operators.py), and [geometry_qa.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/geometry_qa.py) so degenerate/duplicate faces are stripped before operator assembly and inconsistent face orientation no longer kills vertex-normal construction. Docs were updated in [operator_qa.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/operator_qa.md) and [pipeline_notes.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/pipeline_notes.md), and I added follow-on ticket `FW-M6-007` in [milestone_6_surface_discretization_tickets.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/agent_tickets/milestone_6_surface_discretization_tickets.md). Regression coverage was extended in [test_mesh_pipeline_build.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_mesh_pipeline_build.py), [test_surface_operators.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_surface_operators.py), and [test_milestone6_readiness.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_milestone6_readiness.py).\n\nVerified:\n- `make test` -> 43/43 passing\n- `python3 scripts/run_agent_tickets.py --tickets-file agent_tickets/milestone_6_surface_discretization_tickets.md --ticket-id FW-M6-006 --dry-run` -> passed\n- `make milestone6-readiness` -> passed and published [milestone_6_readiness.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/data/processed/milestone_6_verification/operator_qa/root-ids-720575940602483424/milestone_6_readiness.md)\n\nCurrent readiness is `review`, not `ready`. The report says Milestone 6 is usable for Milestone 10 engine work, but with caveats: the real cached mesh needed cleanup of 389 bad faces, operator QA flagged `pulse_final_fine_vs_prolongated_coarse_residual_relative=0.936436`, and the offline verification bundle still contains 0/1 `surface_simulated` roots. That last gap is recorded as follow-on `FW-M6-007`."}}
